article.headline: Duquesne 73, Robert Morris 58
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Bryant McAllister had 24 points to lead Duquesne to its first win of the season, a 73-58 victory over Robert Morris on Saturday, McAllister made his first five shots and had 14 points in the opening 13 minutes as the Dukes took a 26-15 lead. He also posted five rebounds and five assists. Duquesne (1-3) opened the game on a 21-7 run, limiting the Colonials to just two field goals in the first nine minutes. Robert Morris (2-3) cut the deficit to 37-33 after an A.J. Jackson basket to open the second half. But the Dukes followed with a 14-0 run and never led by less than 10 the rest of the way. Tony Lee had 13 points to lead Robert Morris. Freddie Harris added 11 -- all in the first half, when he sustained an ankle injury late. The Colonials shot just 34 percent from the field. Chauncey Duke had a career-high 10 rebounds for Duquesne. The Dukes had all their players in uniform for the first time this season.
